      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with peer review; independent re-run by second analyst confirms reproducibility.",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow documented in a standard operating procedure. An independent FDA analyst reproduced all 11 FEA runs from the documented inputs, confirming no use errors were introduced during model setup or post-processing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic isotropic material model justified for titanium alloy at sub-yield loads; frictional contact formulation validated against published data.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V exhibits linear elastic behavior below yield (~880 MPa). Compression-bending loads in F1717 protocol remain sub-yield for the screw shank. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) between screw head and rod has been validated in prior orthopedic FEA literature. Model form is appropriate for the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of production-lot Ti-6Al-4V; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and Poisson's ratio (0.34) obtained from tensile coupon tests of the same production lot. Screw and rod geometry extracted from CMM measurements of five representative specimens. Uncertainty in material inputs propagated via Monte Carlo and found to contribute <1.5% variance in stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 specimens from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from a single production lot and tested across two independent laboratories. CMM inspection of all specimens confirmed dimensional conformance within ±0.05 mm of nominal geometry, supporting direct model-experiment pairing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicated across at least two load configurations or environmental conditions to assess sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 configuration (static compression-bending at 5 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). Only one test condition was evaluated; no variation in load angle or rate was explored. Achieved level is 2, below the required level of 3. This gap is acknowledged and accepted given the standardized nature of the F1717 protocol and the regulatory context."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions match experimental fixture constraints; loading application point and direction confirmed equivalent.",
      "rationale": "F1717 fixture geometry was measured and replicated in the FEA boundary conditions. Fixed-fixed constraint applied at the block interfaces matches the experimental UHMWPE block embedment. Load application point verified to within 0.1 mm of experimental crosshead attachment. Input parameter equivalency confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percent difference < 10% for each specimen.",
      "rationale": "For all 11 specimens: stiffness E/uval = 1.12 (mean % diff = 4.3%), yield force E/uval = 1.41 (mean % diff = 6.1%), force at 40 mm E/uval = 1.38 (mean % diff = 5.7%). All three QoIs satisfy both the E/uval < 1.96 and <10% difference acceptance criteria. Output comparison is satisfactory."
    },
    {
